<subSubSection pageId="266" pageNumber="267" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="266.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[268,505,438,465]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" refId="ref368401" refString="Rondani, C. (1857) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: II. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars prima. Oestridae: Syrphfidae [sic!]: Conopidae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 264 pp., 1 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1857">Rondani (1857: 121)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1857" box="[630,909,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spathulatus">
<emphasis box="[630,909,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">Platycheirus spathulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the male sex without specifying the exact 
<taxonomicName box="[267,353,475,501]" family="Number" pageId="266" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
of specimens, but giving a single measurement of length: “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">
Mas speciei a me bis 
<taxonomicName box="[1290,1363,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Semel" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="captus">captus</taxonomicName>
prope Parmam
</emphasis>
[the male of the species was collected by me twice near 
<taxonomicName box="[920,1000,510,537]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Parma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="266" pageNumber="361" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Parma</taxonomicName>
]”. We found 
<specimenCount box="[1139,1290,511,537]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">four syntypes</specimenCount>
in this study. Tore Nielsen studied the type material without publishing any paper and considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1857" box="[1130,1407,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spathulatus">
<emphasis box="[1130,1407,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">Platycheirus spathulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Marcuzzi, 1941" authorityName="Marcuzzi" authorityYear="1941" box="[415,839,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muelleri">
<emphasis box="[415,656,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="266" pageNumber="267">Platycheirus muelleri</emphasis>
Marcuzzi, 1941
</taxonomicName>
(T.R. Nielsen, pers. comm., 
<date box="[1161,1349,583,609]" pageId="266" pageNumber="267" value="2013-09">September 2013</date>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
